title: fanoutqa: Of the countries with a head of state assuming office prior to 2000, which are the five with the largest GDP per capita? (c91cb8efeedea700)

chat_history.content: Of the countries with a head of state assuming office prior to 2000, which are the five with the largest GDP per capita?

I'm interpreting your question as asking for the five countries with the largest GDP per capita that had a head of state in office prior to 2000. Although this can be interpreted in different ways, I'm assuming that you are referring to heads of state that were in office prior to 2000 and still in office now. Here are the five countries along with their heads of state:

1. Liechtenstein - Hans Adam II (since 13 November 1989)
2. Qatar -  Tamim bin Hamad Al Thani (since 25 June 2013)
3. Brunei - Hassanal Bolkiah (since 4 October 1967)
4. Eswatini - Mswati III (since 21 August 1986)
5. Monaco - Albert II (since 6 April 2005)
